382  GPS_STATUS_FIX_GPS_PLUS_DEAD_RECK = (int)0x00000400,
383  GPS_STATUS_FIX_TIME_ONLY = (int)0x00000500,
384  GPS_STATUS_FIX_UNUSED1 = (int)0x00000600,
385  GPS_STATUS_FIX_UNUSED2 = (int)0x00000700,
386  GPS_STATUS_FIX_DGPS = (int)0x00000800,
387  GPS_STATUS_FIX_SBAS = (int)0x00000900,
388  GPS_STATUS_FIX_RTK_SINGLE = (int)0x00000A00,
389  GPS_STATUS_FIX_RTK_FLOAT = (int)0x00000B00,
390  GPS_STATUS_FIX_RTK_FIX = (int)0x00000C00,
391  GPS_STATUS_FIX_MASK = (int)0x00001F00,
392  GPS_STATUS_FIX_BIT_OFFSET = (int)8,
393 
395  GPS_STATUS_FLAGS_FIX_OK = (int)0x00010000, // within limits (e.g. DOP & accuracy)
396  GPS_STATUS_FLAGS_DGPS_USED = (int)0x00020000, // Differential GPS (DGPS) used.
397  GPS_STATUS_FLAGS_RTK_FIX_AND_HOLD = (int)0x00040000, // RTK feedback on the integer solutions to drive the float biases towards the resolved integers
398 // GPS_STATUS_FLAGS_WEEK_VALID = (int)0x00040000,
399 // GPS_STATUS_FLAGS_TOW_VALID = (int)0x00080000,
400  GPS_STATUS_FLAGS_RTK_POSITION_ENABLED = (int)0x00100000, // RTK precision positioning mode enabled
401  GPS_STATUS_FLAGS_STATIC_MODE = (int)0x00200000, // Static mode
402  GPS_STATUS_FLAGS_RTK_COMPASSING_ENABLED = (int)0x00400000, // RTK moving base mode enabled
403  GPS_STATUS_FLAGS_RTK_RAW_GPS_DATA_ERROR = (int)0x00800000, // RTK error: observations or ephemeris are invalid or not received (i.e. RTK differential corrections)
404  GPS_STATUS_FLAGS_RTK_BASE_DATA_MISSING = (int)0x01000000, // RTK error: Either base observations or antenna position have not been received.
405  GPS_STATUS_FLAGS_RTK_BASE_POSITION_MOVING = (int)0x02000000, // RTK error: base position moved when it should be stationary
406  GPS_STATUS_FLAGS_RTK_BASE_POSITION_INVALID = (int)0x03000000, // RTK error: base position is invalid or not surveyed well
407  GPS_STATUS_FLAGS_RTK_BASE_POSITION_MASK = (int)0x03000000, // RTK error: base position error bitmask
408  GPS_STATUS_FLAGS_ERROR_MASK = (GPS_STATUS_FLAGS_RTK_RAW_GPS_DATA_ERROR|
409  GPS_STATUS_FLAGS_RTK_BASE_POSITION_MASK),
410  GPS_STATUS_FLAGS_RTK_POSITION_VALID = (int)0x04000000, // GPS1 RTK precision position and carrier phase range solution with fixed ambiguities (i.e. < 6cm horizontal accuracy). The carrier phase range solution with floating ambiguities occurs if GPS_STATUS_FIX_RTK_FIX is set and GPS_STATUS_FLAGS_RTK_POSITION_VALID is not set (i.e. > 6cm horizontal accuracy).
411  GPS_STATUS_FLAGS_RTK_COMPASSING_VALID = (int)0x08000000, // GPS2 RTK moving base heading. Indicates RTK fix and hold with single band RTK compassing.
412  GPS_STATUS_FLAGS_RTK_COMPASSING_BASELINE_BAD = (int)0x00002000,
413  GPS_STATUS_FLAGS_RTK_COMPASSING_BASELINE_UNSET = (int)0x00004000,
414  GPS_STATUS_FLAGS_RTK_COMPASSING_MASK = (GPS_STATUS_FLAGS_RTK_COMPASSING_ENABLED|
415  GPS_STATUS_FLAGS_RTK_COMPASSING_VALID|
416  GPS_STATUS_FLAGS_RTK_COMPASSING_BASELINE_BAD|
417  GPS_STATUS_FLAGS_RTK_COMPASSING_BASELINE_UNSET),
418  GPS_STATUS_FLAGS_GPS_NMEA_DATA = (int)0x00008000, // 1 = Data from NMEA message

1598  INFIELD_CAL_STATE_CMD_INIT_ZERO_ACCEL = 3, // Zero only accel biases.
1599  INFIELD_CAL_STATE_CMD_INIT_ZERO_ATTITUDE = 4, // Zero (level) INS attitude by adjusting INS rotation.
1600  INFIELD_CAL_STATE_CMD_INIT_ZERO_ATTITUDE_IMU = 5, // Zero gyro and accel biases. Zero (level) INS attitude by adjusting INS rotation.
1601  INFIELD_CAL_STATE_CMD_INIT_ZERO_ATTITUDE_GYRO = 6, // Zero only gyro biases. Zero (level) INS attitude by adjusting INS rotation.
1602  INFIELD_CAL_STATE_CMD_INIT_ZERO_ATTITUDE_ACCEL = 7, // Zero only accel biases. Zero (level) INS attitude by adjusting INS rotation.
1603  INFIELD_CAL_STATE_CMD_INIT_OPTION_DISABLE_MOTION_DETECT = 0x00010000, // Bitwise AND this with the above init commands to disable motion detection during sampling (allow for more tolerant sampling).
1604 
1606  INFIELD_CAL_STATE_CMD_START_SAMPLE = 8, // Initiate 5 second sensor sampling and averaging. Run for each orientation and 180 degree yaw rotation.
1607  INFIELD_CAL_STATE_CMD_SAVE_AND_FINISH = 9, // Run this command to compute and save results. Must be run following INFIELD_CAL_STATE_CMD_START_SAMPLE.
1608 
1610  INFIELD_CAL_STATE_INITIALIZED_READY_FOR_SAMPLING = 50, // Initialized and waiting for user to intiate. User must send a command to exit this state.
1611  INFIELD_CAL_STATE_SAMPLING = 51, // System is averaging the IMU data. Minimize all motion and vibration.
1612  INFIELD_CAL_STATE_RUN_BIT_AND_FINISH = 52, // Follow up calibration zero with BIT and copy out IMU biases.
1613  INFIELD_CAL_STATE_FINISHED = 53, // Calculations are complete and DID_INFIELD_CAL.imu holds the update IMU biases.
1614 
1616  INFIELD_CAL_STATE_ERROR_NOT_INITIALIZED = 100, // Init command (INFIELD_CAL_STATE_CMD_INIT_...) not set.
1617  INFIELD_CAL_STATE_ERROR_SAMPLE_ABORT_MOTION_DETECTED= 101, // Error: Motion detected. Sampling aborted.
1618  INFIELD_CAL_STATE_ERROR_SAMPLE_ABORT_NOT_VERTICAL = 102, // Error: System not vertical. Sampling aborted.
1619  INFIELD_CAL_STATE_ERROR_NO_SAMPLES_COLLECTED = 103, // Error: No samples have been collected
1620  INFIELD_CAL_STATE_ERROR_POOR_CAL_FIT = 104, // Error: Calibration zero is not
1621 
1623  INFIELD_CAL_STATE_CMD_MASK = 0x0000FFFF,
1624  INFIELD_CAL_STATE_CMD_START_SAMPLE_BIT = 11, // Initiate 5 second sensor sample and averaging. Does not save sample into cal data.
1625 };

3954 // LE_SWAP: if little endian then swap, else no-op

3957 #define BE_SWAP32F(_i) flipFloatCopy(_i)
3958 #define BE_SWAP32(_i) (SWAP32(_i))
3959 #define BE_SWAP16(_i) (SWAP16(_i))
3960 #define LE_SWAP64F(_i) (_i)
3961 #define LE_SWAP32F(_i) (_i)
3962 #define LE_SWAP32(_i) (_i)
3963 #define LE_SWAP16(_i) (_i)
3964 #else // little endian
3965 #define BE_SWAP64F(_i) (_i)
3966 #define BE_SWAP32F(_i) (_i)
3967 #define BE_SWAP32(_i) (_i)
3968 #define BE_SWAP16(_i) (_i)
3969 #define LE_SWAP64F(_i) flipDoubleCopy(_i)
3970 #define LE_SWAP32F(_i) flipFloatCopy(_i)
3971 #define LE_SWAP32(_i) (SWAP32(_i))
3972 #define LE_SWAP16(_i) (SWAP16(_i))
3973 #endif
